properties.Title: DAYTON, OHIO - Yang Gang Hang (Paint Baby Yoda)
properties.Description:
Join fellow Yang Gang and other Daytonians to paint Baby Yoda at Painting With a Twist at 8010 McEwen Rd Dayton, OH 45458 (across McEwen Rd from the plaza with Whole Foods Near SR 725 [east of the Dayton Mall near exit 2 on I-675]).

Meet other supporters and yang locals all while painting a green-themed painting of Baby Yoda’s face on a 16x20 canvas (smock, canvas, paints, and brushes supplies by Painting With a Twist).

Ages 13+ only (that’s Painting With a Twist’s requirement for this event and their age policy is strictly enforced).

You may bring your own beer/wine/soft drinks/food (none are provided) but no hard alcohol is allowed (cups and bottle openers are provided).

You may arrive 30 minutes early to settle in, snack, get smocked, and socialize. If you are late, you may not be allowed to paint and your payment will be forfeited. Please read the refund/cancellation policy at the bottom of Painting With a Twist’s website page for the event before completing your reservation (you need to sign up here and at that website [completing payment with them] in order to attend).

Reservations are limited to the available seats in the store (and you may not be seated with the group if reserving late), so make your reservations early and call the store (937-331-8340) if it’s the last minute or you’re making reservations for several people (to confirm availability).

Cost is $35 paid in advance via credit card on Painting With a Twist’s website (Click RESERVE NOW, PROCEED AS GUEST, and enter “Yang Gang” in the “Sitting with anyone else?” field on the following website):

https://www.paintingwithatwist.com/studio/dayton/event/2315645/

properties.Venue: This event’s address is private. Sign up for more details
properties.Address:
This event’s address is private. Sign up for more details
Houston, TX 77006
properties.Description:
Hello, Houston Yang Gang! Yes, we need to make calls into the early states to help the teams on the ground identify voters/caucusers!

But there are other ways to help, so if phone banking is not your thing, then please come and text bank, and if that's not your thing, then please bring your writing materials and come write letters for Pen Pals for Yang.

I'm hosting at my office in Montrose, and I'll bring bagels with cream cheese and coffee to help us knock this out on a weekend morning. There is a resident office dog mascot, though he won't bother you, in case anyone has allergies.

There are so many ways to help the campaign that I'm sure we can each find something to contribute regularly together. Volunteering alone can be lonely, and I sometimes slack off, so let's do this together and motivate each other!

Prior to the event:

If phone banking, please review the handbook and get ready here: https://www.yang2020.com/call/

If text banking, please review the handbook and get ready here:
https://www.yang2020.com/text/

If writing letters for Yang, please sign up and get ready here: https://penpalsforyang.com/

If you don't know how to do any of these things, your host has a slight head start, so come anyway and we can help each other.

properties.Title: Santa Clara County House Party
properties.Description:
Please join me:

House Party to Support Andrew Yang

Friday, February 21 at 5 PM

Evan Dowling

1750 Curtner Avenue, San Jose, CA 95124

408-483-3431

Share some food and learn more about why so many folks think Andrew Yang is the best choice for President.

And learn why Yang's proposed Universal Basic Income of $1,000 a month for every adult American citizen would be a game changer in combating homelessness while strengthening middle class families across America, particularly in Santa Clara County.

Bring a friend or two.

In my view, electing someone on simply hating Trump might be successful, but it will not result in an electoral mandate for positive change to address the challenges of the 21st century.

And going back to the status quo before Trump got elected is not the answer, given the crisis of ever increasing income inequality due to the growing power of special interest lobbyists.

We need fresh solutions from an energetic and forward thinking expert on technology.

Andrew Yang is one of the top six finalists in the California primary, polling ahead of Amy Klobuchar, Tom Steyer and Tulsi Gabbard and is closing in on Mike Bloomberg and Pete Buttigieg.

At the house party I will have information on how to vote in the Democratic presidential primary if you are not currently a registered voter or a registered Democrat. We will also discuss why Andrew Yang is the best candidate to defeat Donald Trump.

We can do better and leave no one behind, led by a positive, forward-looking and inspirational tech entrepreneur.

Andrew Yang's slogan for his campaign is MATH: Make America Think Harder. A great slogan, and much needed.

I look forward to seeing you at my happy house party at 5 PM on Friday, February 21.

Best regards,

Evan Dowling

properties.Title: 📞 Call for Yang! ☎️
properties.Description:
### [Call for Yang TODAY!](https://www.yang2020.com/call/)

Hey Yang Gang! Calling early state voters is one of the most impactful thing we can be doing right now to help Andrew get elected. We truly can't thank you all enough for your support and commitment to this movement.

Follow the steps below to get started:

1. Join our Yang 2020 Slack where you can chat with other callers and ask questions by [opening this link in a separate tab](https://www.yang2020.com/join-volunteer-slack/).

2. Everything you need to know about making calls can be found in our Call Team Handbook which you can check out by [opening this link in a separate tab](https://docs.google.com/document/d/17xNaWzkv6ZxpU2dQECmDFc8KcTuNj_ZOAXf9yy8jrJM/edit?usp=sharing)

3. Sign up for as many shifts as you'd like by filling in your info on the right side of your screen! If something changes with your schedule, don't worry about cancelling. The dialer is usually open from 11:00AM CT to 8:00PM CT. Occasionally, it is open for longer, give or take an hour or two. We're *strongly* encouraging everyone to sign up at "peak hours" 3:00PM CT - 7:00PM CT in order to minimize the wait time between calls.

4. Once in the Yang 2020 Slack, go to the #callers_start_here channel where Calling Support will be able to answer any questions you have!
